HEADWORD: Inferno
<hw>In*fer"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. See
<er>Infernal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The infernal regions;
hell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A raging fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>At each sudden explosion in the <qex>inferno</qex> below they
sprang back from the brink [of the volcanic crater].</q> <rj><qau>D. C.
Worcester.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inferobranchian</ent>⟦br⟧
